        <briefdescription>
<para>This function is used to set shutdown manager in shutdown or pass through mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dfxasm" kindref="compound">XDfxasm</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ShutdownValue</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is to set shutdown manager in shutdown or pass through mode. Value can be either 0 or 1. Values are<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XDFX_ASM_PASSTHROUGH_MODE(0) if in passthrough mode<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XDFX_ASM_SHUTDOWN_MODE(1) if in shutdown mode</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>When Shutdown manager is in shutdown mode it blocks the axi traffic that&apos;s going to the Reconfigurable partition from static logic while Partial Reconfiguration occurs. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
